This paper discusses the design and implementation of a benchmarking platform for deep learning models, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The platform also involves hardware and software stacks, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the evaluation and comparison of DL innovations, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the platform, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY).
